<root>
<name>PImage</name>

<category>Image</category>

<subcategory></subcategory>

<usage>Web &amp; Application</usage>

<example>
<image>PImage.jpg</image>
<code>
PImage b;
b = loadImage("laDefense.png");
image(b, 0, 0);
</code>
</example>

<description>
Datatype for storing images. Mobile Processing allows display of <b>.png</b> images. The <b>PImage</b> object contains properties for the <b>width</b> and <b>height</b> of the image.<br /><br />Mobile Processing has additional constraints due to the way images are handled on the mobile phone. A PImage object loaded from a <b>.png</b> file can have transparent pixels, but cannot be modified with the <b>copy()</b> method. A PImage object created in memory using <b>new PImage(width, height)</b> cannot have transparent pixels, but can be modified with the <b>copy()</b> method.
</description>

